elements.2211.03102_627c29831676d35f92c8f7fd83180: Deep Neural Network (DNN) based video analytics empowers many computer vision-based applications to achieve high recognition accuracy.
elements.2211.03102_9c1e8cbfc0df8ff95cc4035b55af0: To reduce inference delay and bandwidth cost for video analytics, the DNN models can be deployed on the edge nodes, which are proximal to end users.
elements.2211.03102_64792339876769e9244ea5d8207ec: However, the processing capacity of an edge node is limited, potentially incurring substantial delay if the inference requests on an edge node is overloaded.
elements.2211.03102_28e6494b51e73110d86a963e038fb: While efforts have been made to enhance the video analytics by optimizing the configurations on a single edge node, we observe that multiple edge nodes can work collaboratively by utilizing the idle resources on each other to improve the overall processing capacity and resource utilization.
elements.2211.03102_adc13ecc648093aa7d818d2ea199a: To this end, we propose a Multiagent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) based approach, named as EdgeVision, for collaborative video analytics on distributed edges.

elements.2211.03102_3cb389c255de8f577c33b43406aa0: We build a multi-edge-node testbed and conduct the experiments with real-world datasets to evaluate the performance of our method.

elements.2211.03102_2c71e6bc85e730b313fccdcecb230: which are compute-intensive and may incur substantial delay for inference

elements.2211.03102_8f33808fecf19cf4e369e6d6cf498: In this section, we present the system architecture and workflows for collaborative video analytics on edge nodes.
elements.2211.03102_5e7b1c674203bcd88676c5f50e7b1: We illustrate the system architecture of video analytics with the collaboration of multiple edge nodes in Fig.
elements.2211.03102_0976af4c70c2bb3862a89725b16a6: The edge nodes are located in different geographical locations to handle the video analytics inference requests from their corresponding regions with the collaboration of the other edge nodes.
elements.2211.03102_0177f71ba444f18f4e10abc86d618: When an edge node receives an inference request, it can either process the request by itself or dispatch the request to another edge node for processing.
elements.2211.03102_3562180645eaeb3b3d63b935deef5: Each edge node consists of the following modules for video analytics: 1) Preprocessing module: a video frame will be downsized to a lower resolution to reduce the transmission delay between the edge nodes and the inference delay.
elements.2211.03102_f0520bc28c2525ece7ff74505b46c: A lower video resolution incurs shorter delay for transmission and inference. 2) Local inference module:
elements.2211.03102_7e9229fcb7debef678a25b8edc254: if the inference for a video frame will be conducted on the local edge node (i.e., the edge node which receives the inference request),
elements.2211.03102_4ce7d4c5788b028b06c43b4f19a95: the preprocessed video frame will be put into the local queue, waiting for the inference by a selected DNN model deployed on the local edge node. 3) Dispatching module: if the local edge node is overloaded, the request will be dispatched to another edge node
elements.2211.03102_cfab31d9c9a0120b534fbcd87c98a: The preprocessed video frame will be put into the dispatching queue,
elements.2211.03102_74632a4fe771d6f189031ebcd2d4a: waiting to be forwarded to another edge node for the inference by a selected DNN model deployed on that remote edge node. 4) Decision engine module:
elements.2211.03102_cc69b2a86323a54855a168e456fbb: the decision engine of each edge node makes decisions on how to process each video frame arriving at the edge node.
elements.2211.03102_f36ec670118f1561fedd159559b32: The decisions for a video frame include inference node selection, DNN model selection, and resolution selection.
elements.2211.03102_92716ac5651d3414bb00c6007d586: The decision engines of different edge nodes can learn collaboratively for the optimal polices.
elements.2211.03102_d4388d1a5974e66a17377353f8af6: When an edge node receives an inference request, the agent makes decisions based on the current system state, and then the control decisions will be applied on the video frame
elements.2211.03102_fb1702fac287b53f5f061a81a53af: The decision engine of an edge node determines whether the inference of a video frame will be conducted locally or dispatched to another edge node based on the their workloads and the bandwidth conditions between different edge nodes.
elements.2211.03102_6f99fa63e51f7bbe23f14d2e9f66f: Video resolution influences video size, and subsequently influences inference accuracy and delay as well as the transmission delay between edge nodes.
elements.2211.03102_3c58d2a109dcc6a1328e81fe69550: Therefore, the decision engine will specify a resolution for a video frame for preprocessing.
elements.2211.03102_baa55e6487b584aed2a3f38b90f58: Different DNN models have different profiles of inference accuracy and delay.
elements.2211.03102_6d5a9015869f5869653d4e1d2f7fe: Large and complex DNN models usually have higher accuracy but longer inference delay compared with small and simple DNN models.
elements.2211.03102_404fb7aaf0379fb261e7f38fb3bfa: The decision engine will choose an appropriate model for each video frame.
elements.2211.03102_cd6aa47eef77f30c227deb1b2264b: These decisions for a video frame are coupled.
elements.2211.03102_5554f0b81c101e27df59d06752377: Moreover, the policy of an agent also influences others.
elements.2211.03102_e41fc6ed7a193d4ba58d0d9ec8f56: Therefore, the agents learn collaboratively to maximize the overall performance.

elements.2211.03102_3ea273ccadeb80c438124037e3fe1: MARL-BASED Algorithm for Collaborative Video Analytics on Edge Nodes
elements.2211.03102_2df18089aabe8b01354550f58246b: In this section, we first present the design rationales of our algorithm,
elements.2211.03102_b3dff9b723227577c425202a1381c: and then present the network structure of the actor-critic framework and the training methodology.
elements.2211.03102_6390c8b576494e10fadc4067b2ed3: We design the MARL algorithm based on the following rationales. 1) Fully cooperative:
elements.2211.03102_b7742d8087c62b298ecfdc6b63cc1: The system has multiple homogeneous edge nodes, which work fully cooperatively to maximize the overall performance of the system.
elements.2211.03102_30cb2c30ece38f6c57b884b37fa54: Therefore, the edge nodes learn their optimal policies to maximize a shared reward.
elements.2211.03102_da9ee6cff952a8ed97d8fe30c673a: Our method is applicable in a fully cooperative environment. 2) Decentralized control:
elements.2211.03102_9c07c43aa0d918aec3af46844dfe9: During the training, the agents are endowed with the other agents' information, which cannot be observed locally, for learning the optimal policy collaboratively.
elements.2211.03102_824fb7ed6637c7dadbeeb93dc42b0: After training, the agents only require their local states to make decisions,
elements.2211.03102_803eac12978cdb77328e4294fe140: which can enable distributed control of the edge nodes and reduce the communication cost. 3) Discrete control:
elements.2211.03102_75090227f77aaa437e3c8ffeed921: The control actions of the agent are discrete
elements.2211.03102_ecda29dbe22db7639cfd04aa17baf: Each agent has three discrete actions, i.e., the selection of inference node, the selection of model, and the selection of resolution.
elements.2211.03102_8d9649e6bb45db716e2dd8476663d: Our algorithm can generate each discrete action by sampling from the corresponding categorical distribution.
elements.2211.03102_923e67cf84c3674b13b5253b4b368: The state space of the system grows with the number of edge nodes.
elements.2211.03102_cc782b6dfa023107a06f80d5b1786: It will be difficult for an agent to learn the optimal policy with the grow of the state space, because the irrelevant information of other agents may hinder the learning performance of an agent.
elements.2211.03102_11111ec2735f1eccc09d6a12e5296: We adopt the attention mechanism to distill the valuable information to improve the performance for multiagent learning.

elements.2211.03102_1ddd0bf6e1eab258510a8e84d6d28: This section outlines the design rationales behind our algorithm and introduces the network architecture, along with the multiagent policy updating mechanism.
elements.2211.03102_0dda78387363818588d11aaff8cba: We design our learning algorithm with the following principles for multi-edge collaborative video analytics.
elements.2211.03102_14e3117a0360b896f99da2862b6c4: The control policies of the agents influence each other
elements.2211.03102_3e606146ed677032b9e9766bdc453: This necessitates a fully cooperative approach among the edge nodes to jointly learn their optimal policies and maximize the collective reward.
elements.2211.03102_fe96272765a839ee62da8cb820f23: During training, agents exchange information about other agents' states, which are not locally observable, to facilitate collaborative learning
elements.2211.03102_9d8760f00f0c0366c630d74f4f5b7: After training, the agents can make decisions based solely on their own local states
elements.2211.03102_6afc6ac09f46cc945a0142044ecb1: This enables distributed control of the edge nodes and significantly reduces communication overhead, and it is particularly effective in scenarios where each edge node functions as an autonomous entity.
elements.2211.03102_0ee4c0d0e7e55a10c0b6daaf02191: As the number of edge nodes increases, the state space also grows, posing challenges for individual agents to learn optimal policies effectively
elements.2211.03102_e44d97fa208dae0d43dc8dcccdd2c: The increasing irrelevant information from other agents can hinder an agent's learning performance
elements.2211.03102_83e4e61a18b778260e2ae6d738ebd: To address this, we leverage the attention mechanism to distill valuable information and enhance the performance of collaborative learning.
elements.2211.03102_b5f2c3123db5ad67a54c7dd851600: In our approach, each edge node acts as an independent agent, equipped with a dedicated actor network and a critic network.
elements.2211.03102_c3f842b1ef55def2af928f94d78bb: The critic network is enabled during the training phase, but once the training is completed, each agent only relies on its actor network to make control actions.
elements.2211.03102_91c82defa15c0fa623f723b2b7578: After training, an agent's actor network operates independently and does not depend on the state information of other agents.
